Ford Motor Credit Co, a unit of FordMotor Co, is raising 150 mln dlrs through an offering of notesdue 1990 yielding 8.275 pct, said sole manager Bear, Stearnsand Co.    The notes have an 8-1/4 pct coupon and were priced at99.931 to yield 62.5 basis points more than comparable Treasurysecurities.    Non-callable to maturity, the issue is rated Aa-2 byMoody's and AA-minus by Standard and Poor's. The gross spreadis 3.50 dlrs, the selling concession is two dlrs and thereallowance is 1.25 dlrs. Reuter&#3;